1777656533240576	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtjAg		item.comment	bn-1cp2	{"body":"Reranker validation against bn-3sco eval harness on a 5-source paraphrase fixture (same shape as bn-hp3u, MiniLM bi-encoder backend, 6 queries):\n\n| metric | rerank off | rerank on | delta |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| P@5 | 0.300 | 0.333 | +0.033 |\n| P@10 | 0.167 | 0.167 | +0.000 |\n| MRR | 1.000 | 0.792 | **-0.208** |\n| nDCG@10 | 0.951 | 0.806 | **-0.145** |\n\nPer-query: rerank wins on `consensus` (P@5 +0.20, nDCG +0.046) but regresses badly on `auth-paraphrase` (MRR 1.0 → 0.5) and `pasta-doneness` (MRR 1.0 → 0.25, nDCG 1.0 → 0.43). Aggregate is a clear net loss.\n\nLikely cause: ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2 is trained on long-form web passages; our compiled kb pages are very short prose (concept page bodies are 50-200 chars). The cross-encoder's calibration gets confused at those lengths.\n\nThe reranker is behaviorally correct and the wiring works — the per-query MRR shifts prove the cross-encoder is actually re-scoring. The model choice / candidate-text construction needs tuning before this is worth flipping on by default. **Default `enabled = false` is the correct posture for v1.**\n\nFiling a follow-up: tune the reranker (try a passage-length-aware model, or longer candidate text construction, or reranker-only-when-top-K-disagrees-with-lexical)."}	blake3:P3d3DG67HyKtXI2KQUa8oUi3RW6aDN2fTnD2Ws6qYQM
1777656536112126	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtjQg		item.create	bn-14tr	{"description":"**Why.** bn-1cp2 landed the cross-encoder reranker plumbing correctly, but on a paraphrase-heavy fixture the ms-marco-MiniLM-L-6-v2 model regresses MRR by 21% and nDCG by 15% — the cross-encoder mis-ranks short prose pages because its training distribution is long-form MS MARCO passages. The reranker is currently off by default (correct posture) but unusable as-shipped.\n\n**What.** Investigate three angles, ship whichever works:\n\n1. **Better candidate text.** Today the reranker scores against the lexical snippet. Try (a) the page title + summary + first paragraph, (b) the best chunk's body (now that bn-3rzz lands per-chunk embeddings, we have a natural per-chunk anchor), (c) just the top-scoring chunk's heading + body so the cross-encoder sees a coherent unit. Re-run the bn-3sco eval after each.\n\n2. **Different model.** Try `cross-encoder/ms-marco-electra-base` (better on shorter passages) or `cross-encoder/quora-distilroberta-base` (tuned for short-form similarity). Cache filename + tokenizer dance is already in `kb-query/src/semantic/onnx_model.rs`; just swap the URL.\n\n3. **Conditional rerank.** Only rerank when the bi-encoder's top-K disagrees with lexical's top-K (high disagreement = ambiguous query, where rerank helps). When they agree, skip rerank entirely (the case where rerank hurt most in validation).\n\n**Acceptance.** Rerank-on aggregate metrics ≥ rerank-off across P@5, MRR, nDCG@10 on the bn-3sco golden fixture. Then flip default to `enabled = true` and update bn-1cp2's docstring.\n\n**Depends on.** None (eval harness already lands).\n\nConfidence: 75% — angle (1) is the most likely fix; angle (3) is a safety net.","kind":"task","title":"[follow-up bn-1cp2] tune cross-encoder reranker for short kb prose"}	blake3:wcAG0QckCxJoC316JyYLAu1_ZFiVRdDo6GwCOR4nIXc
1777657703062937	kb-worker-2n7l	itc:v3:AWKZJ5OZJySZJyUAAAAAQbV67V1WrqAAAAEzAg		item.comment	bn-2n7l	{"body":"Implementation complete in workspace bn-2n7l.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/state.rs` (new): sqlite-backed per-stage state DB at\n  `<root>/.kb/state/compile.db`. Schema: `source_state`, `concept_state`,\n  `stage_state`. Idempotent open/migrate, mirrored after\n  `kb_query::semantic::embed::open_embedding_db`. 7 unit tests cover open\n  idempotency, upsert/lookup round-trip, fingerprint sensitivity, NUL-separator\n  collision-resistance, skip-vs-rerun semantics, stable list ordering, and\n  source_state round-trip.\n\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/pipeline.rs`: opens `compile.db` once per compile,\n  gates `source_summary` and `concept_extraction` on per-(stage, doc_id) input\n  fingerprints. Helpers added: `single_template_hash`, `previous_model_for`,\n  `now_millis_i64`. Three new pipeline tests:\n  `compile_populates_compile_db_after_first_run`,\n  `editing_one_source_only_re_runs_its_per_stage_passes`,\n  `force_flag_bypasses_per_stage_cache_and_refreshes_fingerprints`.\n\n- `crates/kb-compile/src/lib.rs`: register `pub mod state`.\n\n- `crates/kb-compile/Cargo.toml`: add `rusqlite` dep.\n\n- `crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs`: `Compile` becomes `Compile { explain: bool }`;\n  new `kb compile --explain` lists every stage_state row (read-only, no LLM,\n  no lock — safe mid-compile). One Cli struct literal in tests updated.\n\n## Wall-clock comparison (5-source fixture, no LLM adapter)\n\n- First compile (cold):    69.65s\n- Second compile (warm):    0.345s   (~200x faster)\n- `--force` compile:       60.90s    (full rebuild restored)\n\n## Test commands\n\n- `maw exec bn-2n7l -- cargo test -p kb-compile --lib state::`           (7 pass)\n- `maw exec bn-2n7l -- cargo test -p kb-compile --lib pipeline::`       (51 pass)\n- `maw exec bn-2n7l -- cargo test --workspace --all-targets`            (all pass)\n- `maw exec bn-2n7l -- cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` (clean)\n- `maw exec bn-2n7l -- just check` (clean)\n\n## Hash-input recipes\n\n- source_summary    = body + raw_path + summarize_document.md hash + prior model id\n- concept_extraction = body + extract_concepts.md hash + prior model id\n\nPer-stage hash uses ONLY the relevant template (not the combined hash from\nHashState), so a change to e.g. `extract_concepts.md` no longer invalidates\n`source_summary` for unrelated docs.\n\n## Stages NOT integrated (documented decision)\n\n- `concept_merge`: already short-circuits via the existing\n  `compute_concept_merge_fingerprint` (bn-1op).\n- `embedding_sync`: per-chunk row-level dedup (bn-3rzz) is preserved untouched.\n- `captions`: per-image content-hash cache (bn-2qda) is preserved untouched.\n- `backlinks`, `lexical_index`, `index_pages`: cheap walks, not worth gating\n  for v1.\n\n## Edge case worth flagging\n\nWhen `source_summary` cache HITS but `concept_extraction` cache MISSES\n(rare: only when `extract_concepts.md` changes alone), the pipeline must\nre-run `source_summary` because `concept_extraction` consumes the in-memory\nsummary text. The summary call's output is identical so the wiki page does\nnot change, but one extra LLM call is wasted in this corner case. Option:\nread the summary text back from the wiki page on disk to fully decouple.\nDid not implement for v1 — extract-template-only changes are uncommon and\nthis keeps the dataflow obvious.\n\n## Model id handling\n\nThe pre-call fingerprint uses the model id from the previous run's\n`build:source-summary:<doc_id>.json` build record. After the LLM call the\nfingerprint is recomputed with the fresh provenance.model and upserted.\nTrade-off: a model change in `kb.toml` does not invalidate the cache on its\nown — the next compile still hits cache, runs nothing, and the model id\nstays as it was. Matches the existing HashState's model-blindness; first\ncompile after a model change should be `--force` to repopulate. Not a\nregression vs. main.\n\nNOT merging or pushing — leaving for the lead per worker contract."}	blake3:Z00NKgD-ZfrC38m8u7z_kZJocZoWmyI2_Bh4JloaXJA
