1777932871480711	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtpgg		item.create	bn-17t0	{"description":"After bn-3hgs landed parallel concept-body LLM calls, total compile wallclock on /tmp/kb-shake (7 sources) is still ~5:52. Breakdown:\n\n  source_summary:      7 docs x ~6-8s   = ~50s   (serial, LLM-bound)\n  concept_extraction:  7 docs x ~14-18s = ~110s  (serial, LLM-bound)\n  concept_merge:       162s             (single cluster call + parallel bodies, already done)\n  everything else:     <2s\n\nsource_summary and concept_extraction both run inside one per-doc for-loop in pipeline.rs (~1345..1713). Each iteration does:\n  1. cache check (state_conn read)\n  2. LLM call: source_summary\n  3. write source page + build record + state upsert\n  4. LLM call: concept_extraction (depends on summary text from step 2)\n  5. write candidate file + build record + state upsert\n\nCross-doc the work is independent. Within a doc, step 4 needs step 2's in-memory output. So the right shape is: dispatch the full per-doc 'both LLM calls + in-memory artifact build' to a worker pool; serialize file writes + sqlite state upserts on the main thread.\n\nWorker pool cap: same 8 as bn-3hgs (opencode subprocess overhead dominates above that on a 16-thread box).\n\nAcceptance: compile wallclock on /tmp/kb-shake reduces by at least 50% (target ~3:00 or better). just check clean. No regressions on existing kb-compile tests.\n\nFound while smoke-testing bn-14tr / re-shaking after bn-3hgs+22m7+3jdo+24u5.","kind":"task","title":"compile: parallelize source_summary and concept_extraction across docs"}	blake3:hWPyap6CjmxpV9nFQDZ6_FqXRb_9e5Blj81cq2ZIDfM
1777932884709676	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtpwg		item.move	bn-17t0	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:thJlrChYpAO90vLIaqwv0tQXNOILpN8X318-cLpnm20
