1778024315633674	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt1wg		item.create	bn-238c	{"description":"Second dogfood review finding from the installed `kb` binary (`/home/bob/.cargo/bin/kb`, version 0.1.0) against fresh fake KB `/tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW`.\n\nPrior related bone `bn-36hw` is done, but the current installed version still fails in a narrower/newer way.\n\nRepro:\n1. Create a KB with source pages and concept pages linked by compile.\n2. Confirm graph edges exist in `.kb/state/graph.db`:\n   - `wiki/concepts/operational-telemetry.md -> wiki/sources/src-76i-runway-release-playbook.md`\n   - `wiki/sources/src-76i-runway-release-playbook.md -> wiki/concepts/operational-telemetry.md`\n3. Run:\n   - `kb inspect --root /tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW --json --trace concept:operational-telemetry`\n   - `kb inspect --root /tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW --json --trace wiki/concepts/operational-telemetry.md`\n   - `kb inspect --root /tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW --json --trace src-76i`\n\nObserved:\n- All return `graph: null` and `trace: []`.\n- `inspect` does resolve the target and finds citations/build records, but does not surface the graph database edges.\n\nExpected:\n- `inspect --trace` should read the current graph backend and show related source/concept nodes and edges for resolved wiki pages/source ids.\n\nNotes:\n- This is no longer simply \"graph was not generated\": `.kb/state/graph.db` exists and has usable `edges` rows.\n- The bug appears to be in inspect trace integration/resolution against graph.db.","kind":"bug","labels":["dogfood","rerun","review"],"size":"s","title":"regression: inspect --trace ignores graph.db edges and returns null trace"}	blake3:1Ew48tuSEJb59p6VKdbz_UJs33IRLXM7_FVeGXuAs-U
1778024315788267	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt2Ag		item.create	bn-gn9u	{"description":"Second dogfood review rough edge from fake KB `/tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW`.\n\nRepro:\n1. Start `kb serve --root /tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW --port 18544`.\n2. POST JSON with a common API shape:\n   `curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18544/ask -H 'content-type: application/json' --data '{\"question\":\"How should launch expand?\"}'`\n\nObserved:\n- The request succeeds, but the web handler treats the whole JSON object as the question text.\n- Response/body question becomes `{\"question\":\"How should launch expand?\"}`.\n- The generated `answer.md` starts with that JSON object in the quoted question block.\n\nControl:\n- `{\"q\":\"How should launch expand?\"}` works correctly.\n- Plain text body also works correctly.\n\nExpected:\n- Either accept both `q` and `question` keys for JSON bodies, or reject unsupported JSON shapes with a clear 4xx error instead of silently asking the model about the raw JSON object.\n\nUseful pointer:\n- `kb-web` `parse_ask_body` currently parses JSON only when the key is `q`; otherwise it falls back to treating the whole body as plain text.","kind":"bug","labels":["dogfood","rerun","review"],"size":"s","title":"web /ask treats JSON {question: ...} as a literal question string"}	blake3:0POKNZBU4Dr2HKKcaki55XOHjF9hC3inVNyVHSO3yN4
1778024315824356	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt2Qg		item.create	bn-1isq	{"description":"Second dogfood review rough edge from fake KB `/tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW`.\n\nRepro:\n1. Run several commands that create job manifests, such as `ingest`, `compile`, and `ask`.\n2. Run `kb jobs --root /tmp/kb-rerun.HFmTQW list --json`.\n\nObserved:\n- The command exits non-zero with: `kb jobs list: specify at least one of --interrupted, --failed`.\n- This is surprising because `jobs list` reads like the discovery command for job runs, and `status --json` already exposes recent jobs.\n\nExpected options:\n- Either default to a recent/all jobs view, or make the help/command name explicit that this subcommand only lists exceptional jobs.\n- If keeping the strict filter requirement, include the supported flags in the error text and consider a hint like `try kb jobs list --failed`.\n\nImpact:\n- Agents and users looking for job observability hit a validation error at the most natural entry point.","kind":"bug","labels":["dogfood","rerun","review"],"size":"s","title":"kb jobs list with no filters errors instead of showing recent jobs or guidance"}	blake3:PQNxpI_EYfPkaFef6l01oGFydOCr0qP13mz0qk4XHPo
